Joyo Bank to write off 32 bln yen in bad loans . Joyo Bank Ltd said on Tuesday that it would write off bad loans worth 32 billion yen in the financial year ended in March 1997 . The Japanese bank said in a statement that it would post an appraisal loss of 10 . 78 billion yen on securities holdings at the end of the financial year . The bank also said that it would post an operating profit of 43 . 8 billion yen in 1996 / 97 . Earlier , the bank sharply lowered its earnings estimates for 1996 / 97 due to the sluggish Tokyo stock market and the planned loan write - offs . 
